# Auth & Billing Rules

## Before Touching Auth Code

Always inspect:
- `proxy.ts` — middleware, route protection, admin redirect logic
- `app/login/` — login page and form
- `app/auth/callback/` — OAuth callback handler
- `app/logout/` — logout page
- `lib/admin.ts` — `isAdminUser()` implementation
- `lib/roles.ts` — role utilities

### Auth Architecture
- Supabase Auth with cookie-based sessions (`@supabase/ssr`)
- `proxy.ts` is the single enforcement point for route protection
- Admin detection: `isAdminUser(userId, email)` checks against `ADMIN_OWNER_EMAILS` env var
- Admin users hitting customer routes (`/`, `/dashboard`, `/vault`, etc.) are redirected to `/admin`
- Customers hitting `/admin/**` are redirected to `/`
- `/upload` and `/admin/**` require authenticated session — unauthenticated → `/login`
- OAuth code exchange: `/` with `?code=` param → redirect to `/auth/callback`

### Session Handling Rules
- Never create a second auth session source — `proxy.ts` is the authority
- Cookie name for checkout session: `ot_checkout_sid`
- Never expose session tokens to the client unnecessarily
- Logout must clear server-side session AND client cookies

## Before Touching Billing Code

Always inspect:
- `app/api/billing/checkout/route.ts` — checkout session creation
- `app/api/billing/webhook/route.ts` — Stripe webhook handler
- `lib/stripe.ts` — Stripe client and utilities
- `lib/subscriptions.ts` — subscription state machine
- `lib/entitlements.ts` — plan feature entitlements
- `lib/package-plans.ts` — plan definitions and pricing

### Billing Architecture
- Stripe is the source of truth for subscription state
- `subscriptions` table mirrors Stripe data (updated via webhooks)
- `stripe_customer_id` is the mapping key between `profiles` and Stripe
- Webhook idempotency: `stripe_webhook_events` table with `stripe_event_id` unique constraint
- Always check `stripe_webhook_events` before processing to prevent double-processing

### Subscription Status Flow
```
incomplete → active → (past_due → canceled | active)
                    → (canceled)
trialing → active | canceled
```

### Billing Rules
- Never break webhook idempotency — always insert into `stripe_webhook_events` first
- Never expose raw Stripe error messages to customers
- Never use Stripe language like "invoice", "subscription ID" in customer-facing UI
- `stripe_customer_id` must be set before any checkout or portal session creation
- Entitlements must be checked server-side — never trust client-side plan claims
- Upgrades use a separate checkout flow (`/api/billing/upgrade-checkout/`)

## Worker Authentication
- Internal endpoints (`/api/internal/**`) require `X-Worker-Secret` header
- Secret stored in `WORKER_SECRET` env var
- Never expose worker secret to client or logs
